HW5 notebook

Here is the first method for overlaying shape data on a raster.

Use the following packages (install them first), then use them via the library() call: tmap, tmaptools, rgdal, sp, OpenStreetMap, osmdata

These calls are useful: readOGR(), tmaptools::read_osm(), tm_shape(), tm_raster(), tm_dots()

  1. readOGR() your shapefile, store it in a var
  2. read_osm() the bbox of #1 above, store it in a var
  3. do tm_shape() on #2 + tm_raster() + tm_shape() on #1 + tm_dots() to specify point color and size
library(rgdal)
library(tmap)
library(tmaptools)
shapeInfo <- readOGR(".","just_points")
OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
Source: "D:\USC\CSCI585\HW5", layer: "just_points"
with 9 features
It has 11 fields
shapeOsm <- read_osm(bb(shapeInfo))
Current projection unknown. Long lat coordinates (wgs84) assumed.
tm_shape(shapeOsm) + tm_raster() + tm_shape(shapeInfo) + tm_dots(size = 2, col = palette()[2])

And here’s the second.

Use these packages: PBSmapping, ggmap And these calls: importShapefile(), as.data.frame(), get_map(), ggmap(), geom_point()

  1. importShapefile() into a var
  2. convert it (#1 above) to a dataframe, store it in a var
  3. get_map() with a location that’s in your collection of (lat,long), store it in a var
  4. do ggmap() on #3, + geom_point() on #2
library(PBSmapping)
library(ggmap)
shapeFile <- importShapefile("just_points")
shapeDataFrame <- as.data.frame(shapeFile)
shapeMap <- get_map(location = shapeDataFrame[,c('X','Y')], zoom = 16)
Map from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=34.028687,-118.283478&zoom=16&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=terrain&language=en-EN&sensor=false
ggmap(shapeMap) + geom_point(mapping = aes(x=X,y=Y), data=shapeDataFrame, color = "orange", size = 3)
